# Source Control

## Commits
- Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/): `type(scope): description`
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`, `refactor`
- Scope: module or area (e.g. `tts`, `audio`, `llm`, `config`)
- Keep commits atomic: one logical change per commit

## Branching
- `main` is the default branch; keep it deployable
- Feature branches: `feat/description` or `fix/description`
- Branch from latest `main`; rebase or merge before opening PR

## Before Committing
- Run `ruff check src/` and `ruff format src/`
- Run `mypy src/`
- Run `pytest tests/ -v` — all tests must pass
- Pre-commit hooks enforce: ruff, mypy, detect-secrets, conventional commit message

## PRs
- Small, focused PRs; link to issue if applicable
- Ensure CI passes; address review feedback before merging
